  <brief_title>Clozapine-Augmentation With Ziprasidone or Risperidone, a Randomized, Prospective Trial</brief_title>
  <official_title>Clozapine-Augmentation With Ziprasidone or Risperidone, a Randomized, Prospective Trial</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Central Institute of Mental Health, Mannheim</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Central Institute of Mental Health, Mannheim</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We aim to compare the augmentation of clozapine with ziprasidone or risperidone in a
      randomized, prospective manner.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Partial response of schizophrenic psychoses to a monotherapy with clozapine is a frequent
      problem of clinical psychiatry. Current problems are treatment resistant positive and/or
      negative symptoms, as well as side effects. Therefore, different strategies of augmentations
      have been applied. Based on successful experiences in case reports and results of other work
      groups, we aim to compare the augmentation of clozapine with ziprasidone or risperidone in a
      randomized, prospective manner.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
